---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="System Architecture Design — Enterprise Architecture for Mid-Market Operations | Facware"
  description="Generic SaaS architecture doesn't fit complex operations. Facware designs system architectures that align with your infrastructure, compliance requirements, and growth trajectory — before any development begins."
  canonicalURL="https://facware.com/services/system-architecture.html"
  ogDescription="System architecture design for mid-market businesses in Chihuahua and the US Southwest. Built for your infrastructure, compliance needs, and growth. Designed by Facware."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Service",
      "name": "System Architecture Design",
      "description": "We design scalable, integration-ready system architectures for mid-market businesses in Mexico and the US Southwest — aligned with existing infrastructure, compliance requirements, and long-term growth plans.",
      "provider": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Facware",
        "url": "https://facware.com"
      },
      "areaServed": ["Chihuahua, Mexico", "US Southwest"],
      "serviceType": "System Architecture Design",
      "url": "https://facware.com/services/system-architecture.html"
    }
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <!-- PAGE HERO -->
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <i class="fas fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:10px"></i>
        <a href="/#facware_services">Services</a>
        <i class="fas fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:10px"></i>
        <span aria-current="page">System Architecture Design</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>System Architecture Design Built for How Your Business Actually Works</h1>
      <p>Before you build, you need to know what you're building toward. We design system architectures that fit your existing infrastructure, compliance requirements, and growth trajectory — so every development decision is made in context, not in isolation.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PROBLEM -->
  <section class="section" id="problem" aria-labelledby="problem-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">Architecture Debt</p>
        <h2 id="problem-heading">Building without architecture creates problems you pay for later</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Most technology debt in mid-market businesses isn't caused by bad developers — it's caused by good developers building in the wrong direction because nobody designed the destination first.</p>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-3">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Systems that can't scale</h3>
          <p class="card-text">A system designed for 50 users starts breaking at 200. A database schema built for one region can't support multi-location operations. Architecture decisions made early compound — in the wrong direction — as your business grows.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Integrations that were never designed for</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Your custom application was built as a standalone system. Now you need it to connect to your ERP. Nobody designed for that, and connecting them requires rebuilding core assumptions baked into the original architecture.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Compliance requirements discovered after build</h3>
          <p class="card-text">CFDI compliance, data residency requirements, audit trail mandates — these constraints are much cheaper to design for up front than to retrofit into a system that wasn't built with them in mind.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DELIVERABLES -->
  <section class="section section--gray" id="deliverables" aria-labelledby="deliverables-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">What We Design</p>
        <h2 id="deliverables-heading">Architecture that supports where your business is going</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Every architecture engagement starts with your current state, your business requirements, and your constraints — and produces a design that any competent development team can build from.</p>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-2">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Application & data architecture</h3>
          <p class="card-text">We design the structure of your applications and their data models — choosing the right database technologies, defining entity relationships, establishing data ownership rules, and planning for scale from the beginning.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Integration architecture</h3>
          <p class="card-text">We design how your systems communicate — defining the integration patterns (event-driven, REST, batch), data transformation logic, error handling strategy, and monitoring approach before any integration is built.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Cloud & infrastructure design</h3>
          <p class="card-text">We design the cloud infrastructure for your application — selecting the right services, defining security boundaries, planning disaster recovery, and sizing for your workload — on AWS, Azure, GCP, or hybrid environments.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Security & compliance architecture</h3>
          <p class="card-text">We design security controls into the architecture — not as an afterthought. Authentication, authorization, encryption at rest and in transit, audit logging, and compliance with applicable regulatory requirements are built in from the start.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROCESS -->
  <section class="section" id="process" aria-labelledby="process-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">How It Works</p>
        <h2 id="process-heading">Requirements in. Architecture document out.</h2>
      </header>
      <ol class="steps-grid" role="list">
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Requirements Discovery <span class="badge-free">(Free)</span></h3>
            <p>We gather your functional requirements, non-functional requirements (scale, availability, compliance), existing infrastructure constraints, and integration dependencies. You leave with clarity on whether architecture design is the right next step.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">02</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Architecture Design & Review</h3>
            <p>We produce the architecture documentation: system diagrams, data models, integration specifications, infrastructure blueprints, and security controls. We review each section with your team to validate requirements are met.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">03</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Build-Ready Documentation Handoff</h3>
            <p>You receive complete architecture documentation that any qualified development team can build from. We can execute the build ourselves or hand off to your existing team — the decision is yours.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROOF METRICS -->
  <section class="section section--gray" aria-label="Architecture design outcomes">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="results-grid">
        <div class="results-content">
          <p class="section-eyebrow">Why architecture design before development</p>
          <h2>The cheapest bugs to fix are the ones you design out before writing a line of code.</h2>
          <ul class="results-list" role="list">
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>2&times; faster</strong> development when teams build from a designed architecture vs. figuring it out as they go</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Compliance-ready</strong> from day one — security and regulatory requirements designed in, not bolted on</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Integration-first</strong> — every system we design is built to connect with the rest of your stack</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Vendor-agnostic</strong> — architecture documents you own, buildable by any qualified team</span></li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/contact.html#contact-form" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top:8px">Discuss your architecture requirements &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="results-image">
          <img src="/assets/images/facware/resources_facware.png" alt="System architecture results" loading="lazy" width="600" height="450">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RELATED SERVICES -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="related-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">Related Services</p>
        <h2 id="related-heading">Architecture is the foundation — here's what we build on it</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-3">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/custom-software-development.html" class="link-primary">Custom Software Development</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">Once the architecture is designed, we can build it. Fixed scope, defined outcome, single team from architecture through go-live.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/erp-integration.html" class="link-primary">ERP & System Integration</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">Integration architecture defines how your systems connect. We design the integration layer, then build the connections — with the full picture in mind from the start.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/it-consulting.html" class="link-primary">IT Consulting</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">Architecture design often follows an operations audit. We start by understanding where you are, then design where you need to go.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA BAND -->
  <section class="cta-band" aria-labelledby="cta-band-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 id="cta-band-heading">Design the right system before you build the wrong one</h2>
      <p>30 minutes. We'll ask the right questions about your requirements and tell you whether architecture design is the right next step — with no commitment required.</p>
      <a href="/contact.html#contact-form" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Book your free assessment &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .cta-band {
    background: var(--primary);
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: clamp(56px, 8vw, 80px) 24px;
  }
  .cta-band h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .cta-band p {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 32px;
    opacity: 0.9;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
  .btn-lg {
    padding: 14px 36px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
</style>
